statements: CREATE TABLE digital_wallets(id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, balance DECIMAL(10,2))
CREATE TABLE users (user_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE);
CREATE TABLE transactions (transaction_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT REFERENCES users(user_id), amount DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL, transaction_date TIMESTAMP NOT NULL);
CREATE TABLE ExampleTable1 (example_id INT PRIMARY KEY, example_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, example_email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE, example_balance DOUBLE PRECISION DEFAULT 0.0) ENGINE=InnoDB

CREATE TABLE ExampleTable2 (example_id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, example_amount DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, example_date TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES ExampleTable1(example_id)) ENGINE=InnoDB

CREATE TABLE ExampleTable3 (example_id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, example_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, example_balance DOUBLE PRECISION DEFAULT 0.0, FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES ExampleTable1(example_id)) ENGINE=InnoDB
CREATE TABLE example_table_1 (column_1 INT PRIMARY KEY, column_2 VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, column_3 VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE, column_4 DECIMAL(10,2) DEFAULT 0.00)
CREATE TABLE example_table_2 (column_1 INT PRIMARY KEY, column_2 INT REFERENCES example_table_1(column_1) ON DELETE CASCADE, column_3 VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, column_4 DECIMAL(10,2) DEFAULT 0.00)

CREATE TABLE example_table_3 (column_1 INT PRIMARY KEY, column_2 INT REFERENCES example_table_2(column_1) ON DELETE CASCADE, column_3 INT REFERENCES example_table_2(column_1) ON DELETE CASCADE, column_4 DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL, column_5 TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW())
